1
00:00:01,320 --> 00:00:04,320
Today is my 100th day of live streaming

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,160
As I speak into the microphone now

3
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:11,360
A few comments drift across the screen

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:13,800
Some people say I sound good

5
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:16,160
Some people cheer me on

6
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:18,760
But only I know

7
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,520
I can't shut myself away any longer

8
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:51,120
Your voice is so pure

9
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,720
And your emotional expression is delicate

10
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:54,320
Would you be interested in talking about a collaboration

11
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:56,720
Hello

12
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:59,360
The chord progression of this melody is quite unique

13
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,320
Did you write it yourself?

14
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,480
I’ve been waiting for a voice like this for more than a decade

15
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:06,080
Please could you reply me

16
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,880
Listening to your songs, I can tell

17
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:10,640
you have a sharp ear for melody

18
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:14,400
Could you leave your contact info so we can chat about details

19
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,480
I believe I will meet you someday

20
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Will I ever be on stage again

21
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,880
Li Xingyao, right?

22
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,400
Your work station is Number 37 in Area A

23
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,360
Here's your access card and employee handbook

24
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,240
You're the Assistant of the Composition Department

25
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:36,840
Your main job is to organize the music scores

26
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,880
Then sort out the submissions from producers

27
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,760
And also, you need to manage

28
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,120
the booking of the recording studio

29
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,560
Your resume says

30
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,280
you have mild social

31
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,280
anxiety disorder

32
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,200
It won't affect my work

33
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,280
I just don't talk much

34
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,280
Fine

35
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:00,320
At our company

36
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,600
we value ability above all else

37
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,640
Take your time to adapt

38
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,280
Come on, follow me

39
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,360
This is your seat

40
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,120
The new kid

41
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,840
Heard you don't talk much

42
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,640
It's called mild social anxiety disorder, actually

43
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,960
Right?

44
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:59,920
Li Xingyao

45
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,240
Mild

46
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,600
how mild exactly?

47
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:07,240
If I need to discuss work with you

48
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:10,280
will you be able to communicate or not?

49
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,960
I can

50
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,520
Alright then

51
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,520
These are Master Zhou's manuscripts from last year

52
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,160
Please transcribe them into electronic version

53
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,320
It's urgent, we need it tomorrow

54
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:21,840
Oh, and also

55
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,120
I'll send you a file later

56
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,720
Use Pro Tools to separate the tracks

57
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,040
I'm still learning how to use it

58
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:29,760
What?

59
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,000
An assistant who can't use Pro Tools?

60
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,760
Then you need to hurry up and learn

61
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,360
Alright

62
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,600
he just got here, still shy

63
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,960
Don't scare her

64
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:28,640
Let's go for lunch

65
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:38,040
We're going to that new restaurant downstairs

66
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,480
I know

67
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,240
you have pursuits in music

68
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,600
But at least, get your life in order first

69
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,480
Only then will your dreams mean something

70
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,080
Xingyao, just try it

71
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,240
Start live streaming

72
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,200
I'll manage the account for you

73
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,160
You don't even need to say much

74
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,120
Just sing

75
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,080
Sing whatever the fans ask you to sing

76
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,200
I already found a job

77
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,480
You can't even talk to people

78
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,280
how are you going to work?

79
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,440
Why won't you just listen to me

80
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,400
You're always like this

81
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,280
You never change

82
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,200
Or rather, you never change for me

83
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,040
I bet

84
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,360
you won't last a single day at this job

85
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,040
We should let him do more work

86
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,560
Not yet, still a bit short

87
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:30,564
Not yet, still a bit short

88
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,120
You've given him so much work

89
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,000
how could he finish it all at once

90
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,120
You've gone too far

91
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,720
Look how weird he is

92
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,400
seems like he have some metal illnesses

93
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,000
doesn’t look like he can last

94
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,800
Might as well make the most of him while he's here

95
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,520
I didn't know you were such a gossip

96
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:48,120
Is this the professionalism you learned at Xinghe?

97
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,120
Now get back to work

98
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,560
Who allowed you to play here

99
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,200
Give me your toy quickly

100
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,880
Why are you leaving

101
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:44,440
Are you okay?

102
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:45,560
I'm fine

103
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,760
It's so pretty

104
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,680
My mom wove it for me

105
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:52,120
She said this pattern will bring me good luck

106
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,240
When I learn how to weave

107
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,480
I'll weave one for you too

108
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:55,720
My name is Zhou Jing'an

109
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,920
Don't worry, I'll protect you from now on

110
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,560
Zhou Jing'an and his family moved away days ago

111
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,160
Didn't he tell you?

112
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,680
Liar

113
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,680
We really have to go

114
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,200
We'll miss dinner if we don't leave now

115
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,160
Let's go

116
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:54,960
Li Xingyao

117
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,600
This is our company's music producer, Master Zhou Jing'an

118
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,000
You're Li Xingyao

119
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,000
Hello

120
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:37,880
Master Zhou

121
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,320
all these years

122
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,480
you've always been the producer I admire the most

123
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,080
With your talent

124
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,960
even if you sign a good looking puppet

125
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,040
that sings out of tune

126
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,240
you can still make him a star

127
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,960
Selling copyrights

128
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,560
how much money are we losing?

129
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,640
We make original music in the first place

130
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:57,960
If not copyrights, what else do we sell?

131
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:01,040
It's all about looks and fan base now, Zhou.

132
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,400
I get that you look down on those pretty faces out there

133
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,760
but what about Wei Tiantian?

134
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,480
The diva Wei Tiantian

135
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,840
we’ve already came to an agreement

136
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:11,240
As long as you, Zhou Jing'an, produce her album personally

137
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,520
she'll sign the contract right away

138
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,040
Name your terms

139
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,800
But you just won't budge

140
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:25,760
Zhou Jing'an

141
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:28,240
what exactly are you waiting for?

142
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,680
I'm waiting for a voice that stirs my heart to appear

143
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,160
What's wrong? What happened?

144
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:58,120
Nothing

145
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,760
It can't be nothing

146
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,360
Don't think you can hide it from me

147
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:04,920
Tell me

148
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,640
Who bullied you

149
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,480
No one bullied me

150
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,200
Then what's wrong with you?

151
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,080
Don't hide in your room whenever something happens

152
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:13,320
If you don't tell me

153
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,480
how can I help you?

154
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:16,360
Xiu Jie

155
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,280
you always tell me to take off my mask and start over

156
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,640
Do you really think I can do that?

157
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:23,160
I...

158
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,600
In your eyes

159
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,400
Am I just a useless person who can't survive on my own?

160
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,680
That's not... that's not what I meant

161
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,600
Since you met me

162
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,560
I've always been like this

163
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:43,600
No one remembers what I used to be like

164
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:46,840
No one even knows what I used to be like

165
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,360
After all

166
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,800
even I've forgotten

167
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,320
I really hate it.

168
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,760
He actually fulfilled his childhood dream

169
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,880
A music producer?

170
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:26,960
He really seems to have produced a lot of amazing songs

171
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:28,640
But me...

172
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,120
I'm just trapped in my own cage

173
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:51,920
Twinkle

174
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,920
twinkle little star

175
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,920
How I wonder what you are

176
00:15:57,240 --> 00:16:00,040
Up above the world so high

177
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:02,760
Like a diamond in the sky

178
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,760
Xiao Yao, you should be a singer when you grow up

179
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,800
Do you think I can?

180
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:09,600
Of course. Your singing has a way of taking people

181
00:16:09,660 --> 00:16:11,240
Into another world

182
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,680
A pure

183
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,160
trouble-free world

184
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,800
I love singing

185
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,080
As long as I can sing forever

186
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,160
I'll be happy enough

187
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:20,440
I'm going to write a lot and a lot of songs when I grow up

188
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,160
I'll let you sing them just for me

189
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:22,840
No

190
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,280
Let the whole world hear them

191
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:41,360
Why do I have to meet you when I'm in such a mess?

192
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,920
Have you ever forgotten

193
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:22,480
a smile

194
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,520
a cloud

195
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,480
or a promise?

196
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,600
Xingyao

197
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,880
I said something wrong today

198
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:14,160
Don't take it seriously

199
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:15,880
Xiu Jie

200
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:17,680
You were right

201
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,120
I really won't last a single day

202
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,640
That's not... that's not what I meant

203
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:27,040
I've decided to give up

204
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,080
Xingyao, it's okay

205
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:34,320
It's just a job

206
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:35,720
We can always find another one

207
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,000
I've been thinking about it

208
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,600
I really shouldn't have pushed you

209
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,080
You can sing with your mask on

210
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,240
sing whatever you want to sing

211
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:45,760
I'll help you to manage the account

212
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:49,560
Xiu Jie

213
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,480
I've really decided to give up singing

214
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:29,720
Some pasts should be let go

215
00:23:24,180 --> 00:23:25,740
You drew the old alley, didn't you?

216
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:28,700
That alley

217
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:30,580
is exactly as I remember it

218
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:34,020
I just found a reference online

219
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:47,660
Why do you want to quit?

220
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:51,820
I don't think I'm competent for the job here

221
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:55,940
I looked at the music scores you filed away

222
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,820
The annotations in them are very detailed

223
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:00,060
You're completely competent for this job

224
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:01,020
So

225
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,580
What’s the real reason

226
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:04,820
of your resignation

227
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:12,060
I...
